commit.message:
Increase UNDO size buffers

Apparently, large games that change a lot of state can completely run
out of UNDOs during long sessions. Increase the UNDO buffers 16 times.
Hopefully that should be enough. The increased memory footprint and
runtime overhead should be negligible these days (the original limits
were devised back in the early 2000's.)

commit.message:
Fix bogus pending wait_for_keystroke() extended key returns

When quitting a game while wait_for_keystroke() is waiting for input and
running a new game without quitting the interpreter, the first call to
wait_for_keystroke() will return immediately due to the pending CMD_EOF
extended key, breaking things like "pause for more" prompts.

Fix it by ensuring calls to pause_for_exit() and pause_for_more() are
never left in the pending state. Also clear out any pending input event
when a game is qutting, just to be extra safe.

verification.payload:
tree a362cbc428d97332034de73928d25273669c228f
parent 168017e44572d39a2238926b6b9fae25db1f8d8d
author Nikos Chantziaras <realnc@gmail.com> 1684007110 +0300
committer Nikos Chantziaras <realnc@gmail.com> 1684348561 +0300

Fix bogus pending wait_for_keystroke() extended key returns

When quitting a game while wait_for_keystroke() is waiting for input and
running a new game without quitting the interpreter, the first call to
wait_for_keystroke() will return immediately due to the pending CMD_EOF
extended key, breaking things like "pause for more" prompts.

Fix it by ensuring calls to pause_for_exit() and pause_for_more() are
never left in the pending state. Also clear out any pending input event
when a game is qutting, just to be extra safe.

commit.message:
Use linuxdeployqt/appimagekit instead of linuxdeploy to build AppImage

There's no easy way to get ARM versions of linuxdeploy. linuxdeployqt
has ARM binaries, and appimagekit can be easily built on ARM. The
startup shell hook is not supported though, so we need to replace AppRun
with a script that sets env vars as needed and then run qtads.
